<% provide(:title, "#{@course.name} | Get course data") %>
<h1>Download All Course Data</h1>

<div class="row">
  <div class="span10 offset1">
		<p>
			<%= link_to "Download YAML file", data_course_path(@course, format: 'text'), type: "button", class: "btn btn-large btn-success" %>
		</p>
		<p>
		The course data will be conveniently downloaded as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YAML">YAML</a> dictionary, which is a serialized format that can be easily accessed in many programming languages, including python and ruby. Below is an instructive example of analyzing the course data in python.
		</p>
		<h3>Basic Python Example</h3>
		<p>
			<%= raw(CodeRay.scan(File.open("app/views/courses/example.py", 'rb').read, :python).div) %>
		</p>
	</div>
</div>
